$ VBA function: timer

The function `timer` returns a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/single that contains the number of seconds (to two decimal places) since midnight.

{ Trying to gauge timer's accuracy

  The following example tries to gauge the accuracy of the timer.
  gh|about-VBA|/functions/timer/accuracy.bas||

}
{ Calculating hours, minutes, seconds and fractional part

  gh|about-VBA|/functions/timer/printHourMinuteSecond.bas||

}

sa:

  The → development/languages/VBA/modules/Common/Date-Time/timeAccumulator[VBA class `timeAccumulator`] allows to measure elapsed time for different portions within the source code
  using the → Windows/development/WinAPI function `QueryPerformanceFrequency`.

